# GoForms Design System CSS & Class Naming

GoForms uses a modern, semantic, and slightly namespaced CSS class convention for all frontend components. The main design system styles are defined in [src/css/formio-custom.css](mdc:src/css/formio-custom.css) and imported in the `components` layer via [src/css/main.css](mdc:src/css/main.css).

## Class Naming Convention
- All classes use the `gf-` prefix for namespacing and clarity.
- Core components:
  - `.gf-button`, `.gf-button--primary`, `.gf-button--outline`, `.gf-button--danger`, `.gf-button--sm`, `.gf-button--lg`
  - `.gf-card`, `.gf-card__header`
  - `.gf-form-group`, `.gf-label`, `.gf-input`, `.gf-input--error`
  - `.gf-section`, `.gf-row`, `.gf-col`, `.gf-grid`, `.gf-grid--2`, `.gf-grid--3`, `.gf-grid--4`
- Utility classes: `.gf-hide`, `.gf-w-100`, `.gf-m-0`, `.gf-p-0`

## Where to Update Styles
- All design system styles are in [src/css/formio-custom.css](mdc:src/css/formio-custom.css).
- The main CSS entry point is [src/css/main.css](mdc:src/css/main.css), which imports the design system in the `components` layer.
- All templates use these classes, e.g. [internal/presentation/templates/pages/edit_form.templ](mdc:internal/presentation/templates/pages/edit_form.templ), [internal/presentation/templates/pages/new_form.templ](mdc:internal/presentation/templates/pages/new_form.templ), [internal/presentation/templates/pages/dashboard.templ](mdc:internal/presentation/templates/pages/dashboard.templ), [internal/presentation/templates/pages/demo.templ](mdc:internal/presentation/templates/pages/demo.templ).

## How to Extend
- Add new component or utility classes to [src/css/formio-custom.css](mdc:src/css/formio-custom.css).
- Use the `gf-` prefix for all new classes.
- Reference and apply these classes in your Templ templates for consistent design.

## No Bootstrap
- The design system does not use Bootstrap or legacy Bootstrap class names.
- All styles and class names are custom and modern, designed for clarity and maintainability.
